.TH SQ LICON 1 "2026-06-22" "sqlicon 0.1.4" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sqlicon \- interactive shell for Informix
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sqlicon
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Sqlicon
is a command-line interface for IBM Informix databases. It connects directly
using the Informix SQLI wire protocol (no Informix Client SDK required) and
provides an interactive SQL prompt, batch mode, and script execution.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-command \fIsql\fR
Execute a single SQL statement and exit.
.TP
.B \-e, \-\-execute \fIsql\fR
Execute a single SQL statement and exit (same as \fB\-c\fR).
.TP
.B \-f, \-\-file \fIpath\fR
Execute SQL statements from a script file and exit.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help and exit.
.TP
.B \-p, \-\-profile \fIname\fR
Use a named connection profile (stored in ~/.config/sqlicon/profiles).
.TP
.B \-\-profile\-create \fIname\fR
Create a connection profile from the given connection flags.
.TP
.B \-\-profile\-show \fIname\fR
Show profile connection details (password masked).
.TP
.B \-\-profile\-list
List all available connection profiles.
.TP
.B \-\-profile\-update \fIname\fR
Update a profile's fields from the given connection flags.
.TP
.B \-\-profile\-delete \fIname\fR
Delete a profile (requires \fB\-\-yes\fR).
.TP
.B \-\-profile\-default \fIname\fR
Set the default profile name.
.TP
.B \-\-profile\-test \fIname\fR
Test a profile's connection and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-show\-secret
Show cleartext password in \fB\-\-profile\-show\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-yes
Confirm destructive actions (required for \fB\-\-profile\-delete\fR).
.TP
.B \-\-host \fIname\fR
Informix host name or IP address.
.TP
.B \-\-port \fIvalue\fR
Informix service or port number.
.TP
.B \-\-server \fIname\fR
Informix server name (from sqlhosts).
.TP
.B \-\-database \fIname\fR
Database name to connect to.
.TP
.B \-\-user \fIname\fR
User name for authentication.
.TP
.B \-\-password \fIvalue\fR
Password for authentication (avoid in shell history).
.TP
.B \-\-client\-locale \fIvalue\fR
Client locale (e.g. en_US.utf8).
.TP
.B \-\-db\-locale \fIvalue\fR
Database locale (e.g. de_DE.CP1252).
.SH MODES
If no mode option is provided, sqlicon determines the mode automatically:
.TP
.B Interactive mode
When stdin is a terminal (TTY), an interactive SQL prompt starts.
.TP
.B Batch mode
When stdin is redirected (e.g., piped from a file), SQL statements are
read from stdin until EOF.
.SH DOT COMMANDS
The following dot commands are available in interactive and batch modes:
.TP
.B .help
Show a list of dot commands.
.TP
.B .quit, .exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B .mode \fIMODE\fR
Set output mode: \fBaligned\fR (default), \fBcsv\fR, \fBline\fR, \fBjson\fR, \fBmarkdown\fR.
.TP
.B .width \fIIDX WIDTH\fR
Set minimum display width for column \fIIDX\fR in aligned mode.
.TP
.B .width off
Reset all width overrides.
.TP
.B .headers on|off
Toggle column headers in output.
.TP
.B .bail on|off
Stop (\fBon\fR) or continue (\fBoff\fR) on SQL errors.
.TP
.B .timer on|off
Show statement execution time on stderr.
.TP
.B .nullvalue \fITEXT\fR
Set the display text for NULL values (default: "NULL").
.TP
.B .output \fIFILE|stdout\fR
Redirect output to a file persistently, or to stdout.
.TP
.B .once \fIFILE\fR
Redirect the next statement's output to a file, then resume normal output.
.TP
.B .read \fIFILE\fR
Execute SQL and dot commands from a script file.
.TP
.B .explain on|off
Execute SET EXPLAIN ON/OFF to show query execution plans.
.TP
.B .use \fIDATABASE\fR
Switch the active database in the current session.
.TP
.B .databases
List available databases.
.TP
.B .status
Show current session and database metadata.
.TP
.B .schema \fITABLE\fR
Show table columns and raw Informix data types.
.TP
.B .indexes \fITABLE\fR
Show index metadata for a table.
.TP
.B .constraints \fITABLE\fR
Show table constraints (PRIMARY KEY, FOREIGN KEY, UNIQUE, CHECK).
.TP
.B .dump [\fITABLE\fR]
Export table rows as SQL INSERT statements. Omit TABLE to dump all user tables.
.TP
.B .import \fIFILE TABLE\fR
Import a CSV file (with header row) into the specified table.
.TP
.B .tables
List user tables in the current database.
.SH PROFILES
Connection profiles are stored in \fI~/.config/sqlicon/profiles/\fR.
Passwords are encrypted using AES-256-GCM with a key derived from the
user's UID and hostname. Profiles protect against accidental file
disclosure but not against an attacker with access to the same
machine and account.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
Profiles are loaded from \fI~/.config/sqlicon/profiles/\fR.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Connect interactively using a profile:
.B sqlicon \-p mydb
.TP
Execute a single query:
.B sqlicon \-p mydb \-c "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM orders"
.TP
Run a script file:
.B sqlicon \-p mydb \-f migrate.sql
.TP
Pipe SQL from stdin:
.B echo "SELECT * FROM systables" | sqlicon \-p mydb
.TP
Export query results as JSON:
.B echo \e".mode json\\\\nSELECT * FROM products" | sqlicon \-p mydb
